HEADWORD: Blithe
<hw>Blithe</hw> <pr>(bl⟦imac⟧⟦th⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>bl⟦imac⟧⟦edh⟧e</ets> blithe, kind; akin to Goth.
<ets>blei⟦thorn⟧s</ets> kind, Icel. <ets>bl⟦imac⟧⟦edh⟧r</ets> mild,
gentle, Dan. & Sw. <ets>blid</ets> gentle, D. <ets>blijd</ets> blithe,
OHG. <ets>bl⟦imac⟧di</ets> kind, blithe.]</ety> <def>Gay; merry;
